author: ABQnews Staff
title: Perky pets on parade
text:
Pets as petite as guinea pigs and as hefty as horses – dozens of ’em, in fact – proceeded down Corrales Road last Saturday as part of the annual pet parade that’s a part of the Corrales Harvest Festival.
Abby Keller, the parade organizer, guessed that about 200 animals, which also included dogs, a chicken, alpaca, bearded dragons and a donkey and a pig – the latter both candidates for “pet mayor” – joined the procession.
The Joker and Robin — otherwise known as 12-year-olds Joshua Olguin and Jude Chavez — accompany a Bat Car carrying Bristle, a Chihuahua dressed as Batman, during the parade. (Marla Brose/Albuquerque Journal)
